@page "/migration"

<PageTitle>Migration</PageTitle>

<section class="panel-grid">
    <article class="feature-panel">
        <p class="eyebrow">Legacy inputs</p>
        <h2>What we are preserving from the old systems</h2>
        <ul class="signal-list">
            <li><code>E:\TIMELOG</code> contributes the operational workflow: employees, hours, pay history, and starter tax defaults.</li>
            <li><code>E:\TheSWShop\Zephyr</code> contributes the rules patterns for state-specific and local-specific withholding edge cases.</li>
            <li><code>E:\BrassLedger</code> contributes the modern .NET layering and packaging model for a desktop-delivered web shell.</li>
        </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="feature-panel">
        <p class="eyebrow">Tax posture</p>
        <h2>How stale tables are handled</h2>
        <ul class="signal-list">
            <li>Every imported legacy rule is marked <code>NeedsRefresh</code> until we validate and replace it with a current source.</li>
            <li>The schema stores source references, notes, and effective dates so we can audit rule provenance.</li>
            <li>The next milestone should add a dedicated import/refresh workflow for current federal, state, and local tables.</li>
        </ul>
    </article>
</section>
